%20saving%20so%20much%20money%2C%20not%20spending%20it%20on%20gas%20or%20maintenance.%20It's%20easy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EJason%20Luu%2C%2031%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0Los%20Angeles%2C%20CA%20%E2%80%94%20Tesla%20Model%203%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20black%20Tesla%20parked%20in%20a%20lot.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653fe10a96f7540cd069662d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJason%20Luu%20drives%20this%20Tesla.%3Cp%3EJason%20Luu%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20got%20my%20Tesla%20Model%203%20in%202019.%20One%20of%20the%20biggest%20reasons%20why%20I%20got%20it%20was%20to%20not%20have%20to%20go%20to%20the%20pump%20anymore.%20I%20like%20tech-savvy%20things%2C%20and%20so%20I%20thought%20I'd%20get%20ahead%20of%20that%20curve.%20Another%20selling%20point%20for%20me%20were%20the%20tax%20incentives%20at%20the%20time.%20I%20did%20get%20the%20%247%2C500%20federal%20tax%20incentive%2C%20and%20the%20state%20of%20California%20also%20offered%20%242%2C000.%20My%20utility%20provider%20also%20offered%20another%20%241%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20installed%20a%20220-volt%20outlet%20in%20my%20home%20and%20I've%20done%20that%20in%20my%20new%20home%20as%20well.%20I%20know%20that%20that%20might%20be%20a%20deterrent%20for%20some.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20very%20densely%20populated%20city%20like%20LA%2C%20for%20those%20living%20in%20like%20either%20condominium%20buildings%20or%20apartment%20buildings%2C%20they%20might%20not%20have%20that%20kind%20of%20infrastructure%20to%20charge%20overnight.%20But%20then%20I've%20been%20pretty%20impressed%20with%20the%20Supercharger%20network.%20Luckily%2C%20my%20work%20has%20charging%20stations%20where%20I%20can%20charge%20for%20free.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20feel%20like%20when%20people%20think%20about%20purchasing%20EVs%2C%20they%20get%20a%20little%20hesitant%20on%20range%20anxiety.%20But%20on%20a%20given%20day%2C%20the%20average%20person%20is%20not%20going%20more%20than%20the%20full%20capacity%20of%20the%20battery%2C%20and%20you%20wake%20up%20and%20have%20a%20full%20charge.%20From%20a%20charge%20perspective%2C%20having%20it%20installed%20at%20your%20home%20and%20having%20that%20capability%20really%20is%20a%20game%20changer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20to%20the%20average%20person%2C%20you%20map%20out%20your%20day.%20There's%20not%20much%20uncertainty%20in%20terms%20of%20where%20you're%20going.%20You're%20going%20to%20work%2C%20home%2C%20and%20stopping%20by%20the%20grocery%20store.%20You%20can%20plan%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EJerry%20Schotz%2C%2059%20%E2%80%94%20Champaign-Urbana%2C%20IL%20%E2%80%94%20Chevrolet%20Bolt%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20white%20car%20and%20a%20red%20car%20parked%20side-by-side.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653fe0e1356802a56be792c5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJerry%20Schotz%20has%20two%20Chevrolet%20Bolts.%3Cp%3EJerry%20Schotz%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20two%20gas-powered%20cars.%20In%20May%202021%2C%20I%20purchased%20my%20first%20EV%2C%20a%20new%202021%20Chevrolet%20Bolt.%20When%20we%20tried%20the%20EV%2C%20we%20were%20a%20little%20leery%20of%20what%20it%20was%20going%20to%20be%20like%2C%20so%20I%20still%20kept%20my%20Toyota%20RAV4.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20November%202021%2C%20we%20found%20a%20used%202020%20Chevrolet%20Bolt%2C%20trading%20in%20my%20wife's%202017%20Nissan%20Altima%20for%20it.%20We%20were%20fully%20electric%20by%20the%20beginning%20of%202022.%20We're%20surprised%20a%20little%20bit%20at%20the%20vitriol%20that%20we%20get%20from%20people%20because%20we%20own%20EVs%2C%20but%20we've%20been%20very%20happy%20with%20it%20since%20then.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20batteries%20have%20been%20replaced%20during%20the%20recall.%20The%20only%20maintenance%20has%20been%20tire%20rotations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20put%20a%20220-volt%20outlet%20in%20the%20garage%20and%20plug%20in%20the%20car%20there%2C%20since%2090%25%20of%20our%20travel%20is%20local.%20Between%20the%20electrical%20panel%20upgrade%20and%20the%20outlet%2C%20it%20was%20around%20%241%2C500.%20This%20year%20is%20also%20our%20first%20year%20having%20our%20own%20solar%20on%20the%20house%2C%20so%20now%20we're%20driving%20completely%20for%20free.%20Before%20we%20did%20solar%2C%20it%20was%20probably%20adding%20%2450%20a%20month%20to%20the%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20took%20our%20first%20road%20trip%20to%20Branson%2C%20Missouri%2C%20from%20Central%20Illinois%2C%20a%20good%20eight-hour%20drive%2C%20and%20I%20plotted%20out%20the%20routes%20with%20planners%20and%20PlugShare.%20It%20was%20a%20little%20hard%20to%20find%20fast-charging%20but%20we%20made%20it%20there%20and%20back%20without%20any%20problems.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20took%20a%20trip%20to%20Wisconsin%2C%20we've%20taken%20trips%20to%20Indiana%2C%20through%20Tennessee%2C%20and%20Kentucky.%20Electrify%20America%20saves%20us%20pretty%20much%20all%20the%20time.%20I%20think%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20things%20about%20charging%20that%20was%20surprising%20to%20me%20is%20how%20slow%20even%20fast%20charging%20gets%20in%20the%20wintertime%2C%20because%20of%20all%20the%20protections%20for%20the%20battery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegenerative%20braking%20is%20the%20coolest%20thing%20to%20me.%20We're%20happy%20about%20the%20lack%20of%20emissions%20coming%20out%20of%20our%20car.%20We're%20not%20contributing%20to%20any%20sort%20of%20greenhouse%20gases%20from%20driving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felectric-vehicle-owners-advice-realities-cost-maintenance-driving-electric-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698829201000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6536d63196f7540cd0636451%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%2