0In%20October%2C%20Bidhuri%20skipped%20the%20parliamentary%20panel%20meeting%20over%20this%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Framesh-bidhuri-parliament-privileges-panel%5C%22%3Eciting%20%E2%80%9Cprior%20engagements.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20October%2026%2C%20as%20soon%20as%20the%20Ethics%20Committee%20chairperson%20told%20reporters%20that%20the%20Committee%20has%20decided%20to%20summon%20Moitra%20on%20October%2031%20in%20the%20cash-for-query%20complaint%20filed%20by%20BJP%20MP%20Nishikant%20Dubey%2C%20the%20TMC%20MP%20had%20written%20to%20Shonkar%20seeking%20time%20till%20November%205.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20She%20cited%20her%20engagement%20in%20her%20constituency%20due%20to%20the%20annual%20Durga%20Puja%20celebrations.%20However%2C%20setting%20aside%20her%20request%2C%20Shonkar%20asked%20her%20to%20present%20herself%20before%20the%20Ethics%20Committee%20on%20November%202.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20response%2C%20Moitra%2C%20this%20October%2031%2C%20wrote%20to%20Shonkar%20highlighting%20the%20Bidhuri%20case%20and%20the%20contrast%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20direct%20contrast%2C%20a%20very%20different%20approach%20has%20been%20adopted%20in%20the%20case%20of%20Ramesh%20Biduri%2C%20MP%2C%20BJP%2C%20who%20has%20a%20very%20serious%20complaint%20of%20hate%20speech%20(which%20was%20openly%20made%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20House)%20pending%20against%20him%20in%20the%20Privileges%20and%20Ethics%20branch%20made%20by%20member%20of%20this%20same%20committee%20(Ethics%20Committee)%2C%20Danish%20Ali.%20MP%20Biduri%20was%20summoned%20on%20October%2010%2C%202023%20to%20provide%20oral%20evidence%20and%20informed%20the%20(Privilege)%20Committee%20that%20he%20was%20away%20campaigning%20in%20Rajasthan%20and%20would%20not%20be%20attending.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnderlining%20the%20fact%20that%20%E2%80%9Cno%20further%20date%20of%20his%20hearing%20has%20been%20given%20so%20far%E2%80%9D%2C%20Moitra%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20wish%20to%20place%20on%20record%20that%20these%20double%20standards%20reek%20of%20political%20motives%20and%20do%20little%20to%20enhance%20the%20credibility%20of%20the%20Privileges%20and%20Ethics%20branch.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3ESince%20Ethics%20Committee%20deemed%20it%20fit%20to%20release%20my%20summons%20to%20the%20media%20I%20think%20it%20is%20important%20I%20too%20release%20my%20letter%20to%20the%20Committee%20before%20my%20%E2%80%9Chearing%E2%80%9D%20tomorrow.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FA8MwFRsImk%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FA8MwFRsImk%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Mahua%20Moitra%20(%40MahuaMoitra)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FMahuaMoitra%2Fstatus%2F1719556716382097530%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3ENovember%201%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20letter%2C%20made%20public%20by%20Moitra%20on%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%20on%20November%201%2C%20she%20states%20that%20the%20chairperson%20himself%20had%20made%20public%20the%20developments%20from%20the%20first%20meeting%20of%20the%20Committee.%20Thus%2C%20she%20said%2C%20she%20has%20also%20sought%20to%20cross-examine%20the%20complainant%20and%20lawyer%20Jai%20Anant%20Dehadrai%20since%20he%20provided%20no%20documentary%20evidence%20to%20back%20his%20allegations%20%E2%80%9Cin%20either%20the%20written%20complaint%20(to%20the%20Committee)%E2%80%9D%20or%20in%20his%20%E2%80%9Coral%20hearing%E2%80%9D%20on%20October%2026.%20Dehadrai%20claim%20is%20that%20businessman%20Darshan%20Hiranandani%20had%20bribed%20MP%20Moitra%20in%20lieu%20of%20posing%20written%20questions%20in%20parliament%20from%20her%20official%20account.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20has%20also%20suggested%20that%20Hiranandani%20be%20also%20summoned%20by%20the%20committee%20to%20depose%20before%20it%20considering%20he%20is%20the%20alleged%20%E2%80%9Cbribe-giver%E2%80%9D%20who%20had%20submitted%20a%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Esuo%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3Emotu%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20affidavit%20to%20the%20committee%20%E2%80%9Cwith%20scant%20details%20and%20no%20documentary%20evidence%E2%80%9D.%20She%20sought%20her%20right%20to%20cross-examine%20both%20Hiranandani%20and%20Dehadrai%20and%20categorically%20stated%20that%20she%20wished%20to%20place%20this%20request%20on%20record.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20letter%2C%20Moitra%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20Ethics%20Committee%2C%20like%20all%20other%20Parliamentary%20Committees%2C%20is%20not%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20appropriate%20forum%20to%20examine%20allegations%20of%20alleged%20criminality%E2%80%9D%20as%20it%20does%20not%20have%20criminal%20jurisdiction.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20can%20(only)%20be%20done%20by%20law%20enforcement%20agencies.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20October%2026%2C%20after%20the%20Ethics%20Committee%20formed%20by%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20speaker%20to%20deal%20with%20Dubey%E2%80%99s%20complaint%20met%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20the%20chairperson%20had%20told%20reporters%20that%20it%20has%20sought%20help%20from%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20to%20help%20it%20deal%20with%20Dubey%20and%20Dehadrai%E2%80%99s%20allegations.%20Moitra%20has%20asked%20for%20a%20copy%20of%20any%20report%20received%20by%20the%20Committee%20from%20any%20government%20department%C2%A0%20and%20stated%20that%20she%20be%20%E2%80%9Callowed%20further%20to%20cross-examine%20the%20department%20concerned%E2%80%9D%2C%20citing%20checks%20and%20balances%20%E2%80%9Cspecially%20created%20by%20our%20nation%E2%80%99s%20founders%20to%20prevent%20even%20the%20slightest%20misuse%20of%20Committees%20by%20governments%20enjoying%20a%20brute%20majority%20in%20Parliament%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20also%20highlighted%20that%20though%20the%20Introductory%20Guide%20to%20the%20Ethics%20Committee%20had%20warranted%20that%20a%20code%20of%20conduct%20be%20created%20for%20the%20MPs%20to%20follow%2C%20it%20has%20not%20been%20done%20yet%2C%20and%20that%20the%20Committee%20had%20not%20met%20even%20once%20in%20the%20last%20two%20years.%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6in%20view%20of%20the%20lack%20of%20a%20structured%20Code%20of%20Conduct%2C%20it%20is%20all%20the%20more%20important%20that%20each%20case%20be%20dealt%20with%20in%20an%20objective%20and%20fair%20manner%20and%20there%20remains%20no%20room%20for%20political%20partisanship%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698826219000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F01132901%2FUntitled-design-5.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmahua-moitra-ramesh-bidhuri-very-different-parliament-committee%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Bidhuri%2C%20who%20had%20used%20anti-Muslim%20slurs%20against%20a%20fellow%20MP%2C%20had%20informed%20the%20Privilege%20Committee%20that%20he%20was%20away%20campaigning%20in%20Rajasthan%20and%20would%20not%20be%20attending%20the%20hearing.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmahua-moitra-ramesh-bidhuri-very-different-parliament-committee%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'SRK-Sunny%20are%20still%20ruling%20the%20box%20office'%20-%20Exclusive%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698825914000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104882756%2Cimgsize-41554.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fchandan-k-anand-sunny-deols-angry-voice-can-bring-shivers-both-on-and-off-screen-while-shah-rukh-khan-brings-style-to-his-all-his-acts-both-are-still-ruling-the-box-offic