22'Dead'%20Versus%20'Killed'%3A%20A%20Closer%20Look%20at%20the%20Media%20Bias%20in%20Reporting%20Israel-Palestine%20Conflict%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F31163017%2FIMG_0163-1200x600-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20war%20and%20conflict%20%E2%80%93%20when%20disinformation%20is%20pumped%20the%20most%20%E2%80%93%20the%20public%20needs%20to%20be%20informed%20in%20the%20most%20accurate%20way%20possible%20to%20avoid%20hate%20speech%20and%20warmongering.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20essential%20type%20of%20journalism%20in%20this%20process%20is%20peace%20journalism.%20Peace%20journalism%20refers%20to%20a%20journalistic%20practice%20that%20is%20based%20on%20facts%2C%20which%20seeks%20creative%20solutions%20for%20peace%20and%20pays%20attention%20to%20the%20use%20of%20language.%20What%20is%20needed%20is%20a%20language%20of%20peace%2C%20rather%20than%20reducing%20war%20to%20sports%20news%20where%20opposing%20sides%20are%20described%20as%20%E2%80%98winners%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98losers%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20necessary%20to%20avoid%20reporting%20and%20viewing%20a%20conflict%20merely%20from%20the%20point%20of%20view%20of%20immediate%20trigger(s)%2C%20but%20it%20would%20be%20useful%20to%20look%20at%20the%20underlying%20issues%2C%20such%20as%20not%20only%20the%20visible%20aspects%20but%20also%20the%20invisible%20causes%20that%20do%20not%20meet%20our%20eyes.%20It%20serves%20the%20journalistic%20cause%20to%20come%20out%20with%20possible%20consequences%20of%20a%20conflict%20and%20the%20connected%20issues.%20It%20is%20also%20important%20to%20report%20on%20the%20possibilities%20of%20the%20parties%20to%20come%20to%20a%20common%20ground%2C%20instead%20of%20focusing%20on%20their%20differences.%20We%20did%20not%20see%20examples%20of%20such%20journalism%20either%20in%20the%20international%20or%20in%20the%20Turkish%20press.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Fhow-to-deal-with-visual-misinformation-circulating-in-the-israel-palestine-war%5C%22%3EHow%20to%20Deal%20With%20Visual%20Misinformation%20Circulating%20in%20the%20Israel-Palestine%20War%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWestern%20press%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20global%20press%2C%20and%20the%20Western%20press%20in%20particular%2C%20has%20adopted%20a%20pro-Israeli%20stance%20in%20this%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20new%2C%20it%20has%20been%20going%20on%20for%20a%20long%20time.%20In%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.glasgowmediagroup.org%2Fdownloads%2F17-war-and-conflict%5C%22%3E2011%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20conducted%20by%20the%20Glasgow%20Media%20Group%20on%20the%20news%20broadcasts%20of%20the%20BBC%2C%20the%20differences%20in%20the%20language%20used%20by%20journalists%20for%20Israelis%20and%20Palestinians%20was%20documented.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20found%20that%20the%20BBC%20used%20terms%20such%20as%20%E2%80%9Catrocity%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cbrutal%20murder%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cmass%20murder%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cbrutal%20cold-blooded%20murder%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Clynching%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cmassacre%E2%80%9D%20to%20describe%20the%20deaths%20of%20Israelis%2C%20and%20that%20the%20word%20%E2%80%9Cterrorist%E2%80%9D%20was%20often%20associated%20with%20Palestinians.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20similar%20vein%2C%20this%20time%20around%20in%20the%20ongoing%20conflict%2C%20it%20is%20quite%20significant%20to%20note%20that%20the%20Western%20press%20did%20not%20mention%20that%20the%20Gaza%20hospital%20attack%2C%20which%20killed%20500%20people%2C%20was%20carried%20out%20by%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F18013311%2FF8qMGsubQAA8SRW.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22979%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F18013311%2FF8qMGsubQAA8SRW.jpeg%20979w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F18013311%2FF8qMGsubQAA8SRW-245x300.jpeg%20245w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F18013311%2FF8qMGsubQAA8SRW-835x1024.jpeg%20835w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-680542%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20photograph%20purported%20to%20be%20of%20the%20fire%20burning%20at%20the%20al-Ahli%20hospital%20in%20Gaza%20after%20an%20airstrike%20killed%20500.%20Photo%3A%20X%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20fact%20that%20the%20%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F10%2F18%2Fbusiness%2Fmedia%2Fhospital-blast-gaza-reports.html%5C%22%3Echanged%3C%2Fa%3E%20its%20headlines%20after%20the%20hospital%20attack%20%E2%80%93%20first%20to%20%E2%80%9CIsraeli%20attack%E2%80%9D%2C%20then%20to%20%E2%80%9Cattack%20on%20the%20hospital%20in%20Gaza%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20finally%20to%20%E2%80%9Cexplosion%20at%20the%20hospital%20in%20Gaza%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20indicates%20that%20the%20use%20of%20rhetorical%20figures%2C%20or%20in%20other%20words%2C%20euphemism%2C%20to%20reduce%20the%20severity%20of%20the%20violent%20act.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20headline%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3EWashington%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2F10%2F17%2Fisrael-hamas-gaza-un-war%2F%5C%22%3EHundreds%20feared%20dead%20in%20Gaza%20hospital%20attack%2C%20Palestinian%20officials%20say%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20creates%20a%20perception%20as%20if%20the%20Palestinians%20died%20not%20as%20a%20result%20of%20an%20attack%20but%20for%20some%20other%2C%20unknown%20reason.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBBC%20News%2FWorld%E2%80%99s%20official%20Twitter%20account%20(now%20X)%20used%20the%20words%20%E2%80%9Cdead%E2%80%9D%20for%20those%20killed%20in%20Gaza%20and%20%E2%80%9Ckilled%E2%80%9D%20for%20those%20killed%20in%20Israel%2C%20which%20drew%20a%20reaction%20on%20the%20grounds%20of%20double%20standards.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETurkish%20media%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETurkish%20media%20is%20also%20no%20stranger%20to%20expressions%20that%20marginalise%20and%20spread%20hatred%20in%20the%20newspapers.%20Here%20are%20some%20of%20the%20phrases%20used%20by%20Turkish%20media%20outlets%3A%20%E2%80%9CUsurious%20Jew%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9CGreek%20game%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9CRaid%20on%20perverted%20Greek%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9CAttitude%20towards%20Armenian%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20%E2%80%9CInsolent%20Greek%20put%20in%20his%20place%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWith%20regard%20to%20the%20Palestinian-Israeli%20conflict%2C%20newspapers%20%E2%80%93%20both%20with%20their%20discourse%20and%20their%20attitudes%20towards%20the%20parties%20involved%20%E2%80%93%20have%20shown%20a%20journalistic%20approach%20that%20is%20far%20from%20being%20solution-oriented.%20They%20resorted%20to%20propaganda%20and%20agitation%20whilst%20describing%20the%20violence%20in%20its%20most%20detailed%20form.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20look%20at%20the%20Western%20media%2C%20we%20know%20that%20they%20are%20pro-Israel%20as%20if%20they%20are%20supporting%20a%20football%20team%2C%20while%20the%20Arab%20media%20outlets%20have%20been%20publishing%20their%20content%20with%20a%20Palestine%20slant.%20Turkey%2C%20as%20a%20Muslim%20country%2C%20also%20prefers%20a%20pro-Palestinian%20slant%2C%20and%20the%20choice%20of%20which%20news%20to%20report%20and%20how%20to%20report%20is%20naturally%20determined%20by%20the%20favouring%20of%20%E2%80%9Creligious%20brotherhood%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20conflict%20creates%20a%20dualism%20between%20Muslims%20and%20non-Muslims.%20In%20such%20a%20situation%2C%20news%20items%20justify%20the%20violence%20of%20the%20side%20they%20favour%20and%20blame%20the%20other%20side%2C%20to%20convey%20the%20message%20that%20%E2%80%98we%20are%20the%20good%20ones%2C%20they%20are%20the%20bad%20ones%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20use%20of%20emotional%20words%20%E2%80%93%20such%20as%20%E2%80%9Cgenocide%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cmassacre%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cmurderer%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cexile%20or%20death%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cpersecution%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cblood%20and%20destruction%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwe%20cut%20the%20lifeblood%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20lions%20of%20the%20ummah%20hit%20the%20murderer%20Israel%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20have%20been%20seen%20in%20the%20headlines%20in%20Turkish%20media%20since%20October%207%2C%20when%20the%20latest%20conflict%20began.%20Such%20use%20of%20language%20does%20nothing%20but%20fall%20into%20the%20trap%20of%20sensationalism%20and%20exaggeration.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAgain%2C%20the%20headlines%20in%20our%20press%20such%20as%20%E2%80%9CDenaturalise%20the%20Zionist%20henchmen%E2%80%9D%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20encourage%20hatred%20against%20the%20Jewish%20minority%20in%20Turkey%20and%20to%20prepare%20an%20environment%20to%20incite%20acts%20of%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhat%20these%20examples%20have%20in%20common%20is%20that%20they%20incite%20violence%20and%20war%2C%20and%20are%20antagonising.%20Such%20discourses%20instil%20fear%20among%20Turkish%20citizens%20of%20Jewish%20descent%2C%20damage%20their%20honour%2C%20and%20also%20disrupt%20peace.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Ftyahuditoplumu%2Fstatus%2F1714595099617661223%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E%20made%20by%20the%20Jewish%20community%20of%20Turkey%20on%20its%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%20account%20is%20extremely%20prudent%20and%20very%20appropriate%20in%20this%20context.%20The%20Turkish%20Chief%20Rabbinate%20Foundation%20wrote%20on%20X%20(Twitter)%20in%20Turkish%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20strongly%20reject%20and%20condemn%20the%20targeting%20and%20murder%20of%20innocent%20civilians%20under%20any%20circumstances%20and%20wherever%20they%20occur%20%E2%80%93%20especially%20hospitals%2C%20schools%2C%20nursing%20homes%2C%20etc.%20This%20is%20a%20situation%20that%20eliminates%20the%20most%20basic%20expectation%20of%20human%20beings%20%E2%80%93%20the%20right%20to%20life%20%E2%80%93%20according%20to%20international%20law%2C%20it%20is%20accepted%2C%20defended%2C%20and%20excused.%20There%20is%20NO%20side%20to%20it.%20In%20this%20context%2C%20our%20state%20supports%20the%20efforts%20of%20the%20Republic%20of%20Turkey%20since%20the%20first%20day%20to%20ensure%20urgent%20peace%2C%20and%20we%20wish%20that%20all%20people%20will%20be%20brought%20to%20permanent%20peace%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20some%20fundamental%20points%20that%20should%20not%20be%20ignored%3A%20the%20historical%20background%20of%20the%20Israeli-Palestinian%20conflict%2C%20the%20fact%20that%20violence%20does%20not%20occur%20unilaterally%20by%20itself%2C%20and%20the%20common%20or%20conflicting%20interests%20of%20the%20parties%20involved%20in%20this%20conflict%20outside%20Israel%20and%20Palestine.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHere%2C%20the%20biggest%20task%20for%20the%20media%20is%20to%20put%20forward%20non-violent%20solutions%20and%20proposals%20in%20the%20face%20of%20this%20conflict%20and%20to%20provide%20a%20platform%20for%20discussion.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20wrong%20as%20it%20is%20to%20equate%20Jews%20with%20the%20Israeli%20government%20and%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%2C%20it%20is%20equally%20problematic%20to%20equate%20Hamas%20with%20Palestinians%20(civilians%2C%20women%2C%20and%20children).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELimiting%20the%20reporting%20to%20the%20Hamas%20attack%20on%20October%207%20and%20framing%20the%20decades-long%20Palestinian%20conflict%20in%20detail%20with%20the%20use%20of%20%E2%80%9Cselective%20sourcing%E2%80%9D%2C%20far%20from%20what%20it%20deserves%2C%20can%20present%20events%20in%20favour%20of%20one%20side%20and%20against%20the%20other.%20Why%2C%20for%20example%2C%20do%20we%20not%20see%20the%20pro-peace%20sectors%20of%20both%20sides%20in%20the%20news%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhere%20are%20the%20Jews%20criticising%20the%20Israeli%20government%2C%20and%20the%20Palestinians%20and%20Arabs%20criticising%20Hamas%3F%20Why%20are%20opposing%20pacifist%20discourses%20invisible%20in%20the%20media%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20journalistic%20ethics%20require%20journalists%20to%20verify%20their%20reporting.%20Otherwise%2C%20journalism%20falls%20into%20the%20trap%20of%20propaganda%20and%20fiction.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20Israel%20claimed%20that%20the%20attack%20on%20the%20hospital%20in%20Gaza%20was%20due%20to%20a%20rocket%20fired%20by%20Hamas%2C%20Israel%20was%20blamed%20by%20Hamas%20for%20the%20attack.%20A%20group%20of%20experts%20from%20the%20United%20Nations%20could%20bring%20out%20the%20truth%2C%20as%20such%20experts%20had%20done%20in%20the%20past%20in%20similar%20situations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDecontextualised%20reporting%20on%20the%20Palestinian%20conflict%20and%20the%20deprivation%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20people%20of%20their%20most%20basic%20rights%20for%20years%20make%20it%20impossible%20to%20understand%20the%20underlying%20motivations%20or%20causes%20of%20the%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EReporting%20that%20ignores%20the%20ongoing%20war%20in%20the%20region%2C%20human%20rights%2C%20civil%20rights%2C%20political%20and%20economic%20rights%2C%20etc.%2C%20and%20labels%20one%20side%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98oppressor%E2%80%99%20and%20the%20other%20side%20as%20a%20victim%20is%20nothing%20but%20simplistic%20and%20bad%20reporting.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20observe%20that%20the%20international%20media%20and%20Turkish%20media%2C%20with%20their%20unequal%20and%20unbalanced%20perspective%2C%20do%20not%20strive%20for%20justice%2C%20balance%2C%20consistency%2C%20and%20inclusiveness%20in%20their%20reportage.%20Instead%2C%20they%20demonise%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20Israeli%20and%20Palestinian%20people%20are%20fed%20up%20with%20violence.%20The%20Israeli%20government%20and%20Hamas%20accusing%20each%20other%20of%20terrorism%2C%20massacres%2C%20and%20genocide%20are%20the%20biggest%20obstacles%20on%20the%20road%20to%20peace.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EState%20administrators%20have%20a%20great%20duty%20in%20this%20regard%2C%20they%20should%20not%20cause%20more%20civilian%20deaths%20with%20provocative%20speeches%20and%20by%20setting%20their%20own%20ideological%20apparatus%20%E2%80%93%20the%20media%20%E2%80%93%20on%20fire.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EYasemin%20Giritli%20%C4%B0nceo%C4%9Flu%20is%20a%20Visiting%20Professor%20of%20Media%20Studies%20at%20the%20LSE%20Media%20and%20Communication%20Department.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698823317000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F31163017%2FIMG_0163-1200x600-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fdead-versus-killed-a-closer-look-at-the-media-bias-in-reporting-israel-palestine-conflict%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Depending%20upon%20the%20side%20they%20favour%2C%20media%20outlets%20have%20been%20tactfully%20employing%20language%2C%20which%20is%20resulting%20in%20hate%20speech%20and%20warmongering.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fdead-versus-killed-a-closer-look-at-the-media-bias-in-reporting-israel-palestine-conflict%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Sushmita%20Sen%20on%20people%20naming%20kids%20Aarya-%20Exclusive%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698823294000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104880986%2Cimgsize-17628.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fsushmita-sen-people-naming-their-daughters-aarya-is-a-big-compliment%2Farticleshow%2F104881007.cms%22%2C%22summa