rength%20after%202014.%20The%20group's%20leadership%20is%20formed%20by%20the%20Houthi%20tribe%20and%20is%20currently%20led%20by%20Abdul-Malik%20Badruldeen%20al-Houthi.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELebanon%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EFounded%20in%20the%20early%201980s%2C%20Hezbollah%20holds%20the%20distinction%20of%20being%20Iran's%20first%20proxy%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%20The%20group%20is%20funded%20militarily%20and%20financially%20by%20the%20Revolutionary%20Guards.%20Hezbollah%20shares%20Tehran's%20Shiite%20Islamist%20ideals%20and%20recruits%20mostly%20among%20the%20Lebanese%20Shiite%20Muslims.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHezbollah%20was%20formed%20to%20fight%20Israeli%20forces%20that%20had%20invaded%20Lebanon%20in%201982.%20It%20has%20routinely%20carried%20out%20suicide%20attacks%20against%20US%20personnel%20and%20its%20embassies%20in%20Lebanon.%20By%202020%2C%20Hezbollah%2C%20with%20at%20least%20130%2C000%20rockets%20and%20missiles%2C%20became%20the%20world's%20most%20heavily%20armed%20non-state%20actor%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Center%20for%20Strategic%20and%20International%20Studies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2019-08%2Fi1hs18f_hezbollah-chief-hassan-nasrallah_625x300_26_August_19.jpg%3Fim%3DFitAndFill%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EHezbollah%20maintains%20deep%20and%20close%20ties%20with%20other%20Iran-backed%20groups%20in%20the%20region%20including%20Hamas%20and%20the%20Islamic%20Jihad.%20Following%20the%20October%207%20attacks%20on%20Israel%20by%20Hamas%2C%20and%20the%20subsequent%20Israeli%20retaliation%2C%20Hezbollah%20joined%20the%20fight%20%26quot%3Bin%20solidarity%26quot%3B%20with%20the%20Palestinian%20people.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESyria%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3ESyria's%20Assad%20family%2C%20a%20Shia%20offshoot%2C%20has%20long%20relied%20on%20its%20alliance%20with%20Iran%20to%20stay%20in%20power.%20This%20alliance%20has%20been%20especially%20beneficial%20since%202011%2C%20when%20President%20Bashar%20al-Assad%20faced%20an%20anti-government%20uprising%20and%20a%20civil%20war%20with%20Sunni%20extremists.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20Syria%20plummetted%20into%20chaos%20in%202011%2C%20Iran%20has%20been%20accused%20by%20Israel%20of%20providing%20around%2080%2C000%20fighting%20personnel%20to%20al-Assad's%20army%20while%20Russia%20provided%20air%20support.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202014%2C%20the%20Revolutionary%20Guards%20formed%20the%20Zaynabiyoun%20Brigade%2C%20a%20Pakistani%20Shiite%20militia%20group%20made%20up%20of%20Pakistanis%20living%20in%20Iran%20as%20well%20as%20the%20tribal%20areas%20of%20Pakistan%2C%20which%20fought%20alongside%20al-Assad's%20forces%20against%20rebel%20militias.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Fatemiyoun%20Division%2C%20a%20group%20of%20Afghan%20Hazara%20fighters%2C%20was%20formed%20in%20the%201980s%2C%20ceased%20to%20exist%20in%20the%201990s%2C%20and%20was%20reestablished%20by%20the%20Revolutionary%20Guards%20in%202012.%20Since%202014%2C%20Iran%20has%20deployed%20the%20Fatemiyoun%20Division%20to%20Syria%20to%20fight%20for%20the%20Syrian%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIraq%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20US%20invasion%20of%20Iraq%20in%202003%2C%20Iran%20expanded%20its%20influence%20on%20its%20former%20enemy%2C%20establishing%20loyal%20militias%2C%20gaining%20significant%20political%20clout%2C%20and%20reaping%20economic%20rewards.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202007%2C%20the%20Revolutionary%20Guards%20created%20the%20Kataib%20Hezbollah%2C%20a%20Shiite%20militia.%20US%20declared%20the%20Kataib%20Hezbollah%20as%20a%20'Foreign%20Terrorist%20Organisation'%20in%202009%20and%20sanctioned%20its%20Secretary%20General%2C%20Abu%20Mahdi%20al%20Muhandis%2C%20for%20violence%20against%20US-led%20coalition%20forces%20in%20Iraq.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202014%2C%20the%20Kataib%20Hezbollah%20joined%20Iraq's%20Popular%20Mobilization%20Forces%20(PMF)%20to%20fight%20Islamic%20State%20(IS)%20fighters%20but%20maintained%20close%20relations%20with%20the%20leadership%20in%20Tehran.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFrom%202007%20to%202011%20and%20again%20from%202018%20to%202020%2C%20the%20Kataib%20Hezbollah%2C%20with%20Iran's%20backing%2C%20targetted%20US%20forces%20and%20its%20allies%20in%20Iraq%20with%20a%20series%20of%20sophisticated%20attacks.%20A%202019%20rocket%20attack%20killed%20a%20US%20civilian%20contractor%20and%20injured%20four%20US%20soldiers%20at%20a%20military%20base%20in%20Kirkuk.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202006%2C%20the%20Revolutionary%20Guards%20and%20Hezbollah%20founded%20and%20trained%20the%20Asaib%20Ahl%20al%20Haq%20a%20Shiite%20militia.%20When%20the%20US%20recalled%20its%20forces%20from%20Iraq%20between%202006%20and%202011%2C%20the%20group%20launched%20over%206%2C000%20attacks%20on%20US%20and%20its%20allies.%20With%20around%2020%2C000%20personnel%2C%20the%20Asaib%20Ahl%20al%20Haq%20grew%20to%20become%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20Iran-backed%20militias%20in%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20the%20Revolutionary%20Guards%20armed%20and%20funded%20other%20Shiite%20groups%20in%20Iraq%20such%20as%20the%20Harakat%20Hezbollah%20al%20Nujaba%2C%20the%20Badr%20Organization%20and%20the%20Kataib%20Sayyad%20al%20Shuhada.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EGaza%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Palestinian%20territories%2C%20Iran%20has%20for%20decades%20fought%20a%20shadow%20war%20against%20Israel.%20Hamas%2C%20the%20Palestinian%20group%20that%20carried%20out%20the%20October%207%20attacks%20on%20Israel%20is%20believed%20to%20be%20funded%20by%20Tehran%20where%20it%20opened%20an%20office%20in%20the%201990s.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERelations%20between%20Iran%20and%20Hamas%20soured%20in%202012%20after%20the%20Palestinian%20group%20refused%20to%20back%20the%20al-Assad%20regime%20in%20Syria.%20It%20led%20to%20Iraq%20temporarily%20cutting%20funding%20to%20Hamas%20before%20resuming%20it%20in%202017.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Palestinian%20Islamic%20Jihad%20(PIJ)%20drew%20inspiration%20from%20the%20Iranian%20Revolution.%20According%20to%20the%20US%20State%20Department%2C%20it%20is%20Iran%20that%20funds%20the%20Islamic%20Jihad's%20budget%2C%20exactly%20like%20it%20reportedly%20does%20for%20Hamas%20and%20Hezbollah.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20State%20Department%20said%20in%202020%20that%20Iran%20provided%20more%20than%20%24100%20million%20annually%20to%20Palestinian%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESaudi%20Arabia%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%201987%2C%20the%20Revolutionary%20Guards%20founded%20the%20Shiite%20militant%20group%20Hezbollah%20al%20Hejaz%20in%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20one%20of%20Iran's%20primary%20political%20proponents%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%20The%20US%20sanctioned%20four%20of%20its%20leaders%20for%20the%20deadly%201996%20Khobar%20Tower%20bombing%20that%20killed%2019%20US%20Air%20Force%20personnel%20and%20Injured%20over%20350%20others.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Justice%20Department%20ordered%20Iran%20to%20pay%20%24254%20million%20to%20the%20families%20of%20the%20victims.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBahrain%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EFunded%20and%20trained%20by%20Iran%2C%20the%20Al%20Ashtar%20Brigades%20is%20a%20militia%20based%20in%20the%20Gulf%20country%20of%20Bahrain.%20In%202014%2C%20the%20Al%20Ashtar%20Brigaded%20were%20behind%20the%20bomb%20attack%20that%20killed%20two%20police%20officers.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698820320000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-11%2F1vhi5j5_ayatollah-khomeini-getty-_625x300_01_November_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F