%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EAl%20Jazeera%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20refugee%20camp%20covers%20an%20area%20of%20only%201.4%20square%20kilometres%20but%20houses%20some%20116%2C000%20registered%20refugees.%20The%20Israeli%20military%20has%20repeatedly%20struck%20the%20camp%20since%20the%20start%20of%20the%20war%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Gaza%20health%20ministry%20said%20that%20at%20least%208%2C525%20people%20have%20been%20killed%20in%20Israeli%20strikes%20since%20October%208%20and%20two-thirds%20of%20those%20killed%20are%20women%20and%20children.%20At%20least%203%2C542%20children%20and%202%2C187%20women%20were%20among%20the%20dead.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20health%20ministry%20spokesperson%20Ashraf%20Al-Qudra%20said%20130%20healthcare%20staff%20were%20killed%20and%2015%20hospitals%20are%20now%20out%20of%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUN%20secretary%20general%20Antonio%20Guterres%20said%20the%20escalation%20of%20conflict%20between%20Israel%20and%20armed%20Palestinian%20groups%20will%20only%20increase%20the%20immense%20suffering%20of%20civilians.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EI%20am%20deeply%20alarmed%20by%20the%20intensification%20of%20the%20conflict%20between%20Israel%20and%20Hamas%20and%20other%20Palestinian%20armed%20groups%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWith%20too%20many%20Israeli%20and%20Palestinian%20lives%20already%20lost%2C%20this%20escalation%20only%20increases%20the%20immense%20suffering%20of%20civilians.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Ant%C3%B3nio%20Guterres%20(%40antonioguterres)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fantonioguterres%2Fstatus%2F1719390809462898957%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EOctober%2031%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20WHO%20official%20told%20a%20press%20briefing%20in%20Geneva%20that%20people%20in%20Gaza%20are%20facing%20a%20looming%20%E2%80%9Cpublic%20health%20catastrophe.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIsrael%20tightened%20its%20blockade%20on%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20home%20to%202.3%20million%20people%2C%20following%20the%20Hamas%20terror%20attacks%20on%20October%207.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlthough%20more%20than%20150%20trucks%20carrying%20humanitarian%20supplies%20have%20been%20allowed%20to%20enter%20the%20territory%20from%20Egypt%20over%20the%20past%20few%20days%2C%20aid%20workers%20say%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20enough.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDamage%20to%20water%20and%20sanitation%20infrastructure%2C%20overcrowding%20and%20mass%20displacement%20are%20compounding%20an%20already%20dire%20humanitarian%20situation%20in%20the%20territory%2C%20they%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20WHO%20spokesperson%20said%20fuel%20was%20urgently%20needed%20to%20run%20generators%20at%20clinics%2C%20to%20treat%20water%20and%20for%20emergency%20vehicles.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698771622000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F31221251%2FScreenshot-2023-10-31-at-10.12.04%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fisraeli-strike-jabalia-refugee-camp-gaza%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Gaza%20health%20ministry%20said%20that%20at%20least%208%2C525%20people%20have%20been%20killed%20in%20Israeli%20strikes%20and%20two-thirds%20of%20those%20killed%20are%20women%20and%20children.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fisraeli-strike-jabalia-refugee-camp-gaza%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%E2%80%99s%20Behaviour%20on%20the%20World%20Stage%20Is%20Not%20Helping%20Its%20Interests%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F26083945%2FF6NVFb_XAAAuHrW.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20government%20has%20abstained%20from%20calling%20for%20an%20end%20to%20the%20violence%20in%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20in%20a%20UN%20General%20Assembly%20resolution%20in%20order%20to%20avoid%20upsetting%20the%20United%20States.%20India%20was%20told%20by%20the%20new%20Maldives%20leader%20to%20remove%20our%20soldiers%20from%20that%20country.%20Qatar%20sentenced%20eight%20Navy%20veterans%20to%20death.%20Sri%20Lanka%20allowed%20a%20Chinese%20spy%20ship%20to%20dock%20in%20Colombo%20despite%20India%E2%80%99s%20objections.%20Bhutan%20has%20said%20it%20was%20about%20to%20conclude%20boundary%20negotiations%20with%20China%2C%20including%20on%20Doklam.%20Nepal%20cannot%20use%20its%20new%20Gautam%20Buddha%20airport%20because%20India%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20allow%20overflight%20of%20large%20planes.%20Canada%20has%20said%20it%20would%20not%20be%20able%20to%20normalise%20visas%20for%20Indians%20till%202024.%20These%20things%20have%20happened%20in%20the%20space%20of%20a%20few%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAll%20South%20Asian%20nations%20except%20India%20voted%20to%20end%20the%20violence%20in%20Gaza%2C%20including%20Nepal%2C%20Sri%20Lanka%20and%20Bhutan%2C%20which%20traditionally%20votes%20with%20India.%20The%2070%20Indian%20military%20personnel%20in%20the%20Maldives%20who%20will%20now%20return%20maintain%20radar%20stations%20and%20surveillance%20aircraft%2C%20and%20Indian%20warships%20help%20patrol%20the%20Maldives%E2%80%99%20exclusive%20economic%20zone.%20The%20reason%20we%20have%20been%20told%20to%20go%20is%20that%20the%20Maldives%20wants%20to%20favour%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhether%20we%20are%20running%20a%20successful%20foreign%20policy%2C%20as%20fans%20of%20the%20external%20affairs%20minister%20believe%2C%20or%20we%20are%20ruining%20India%E2%80%99s%20global%20reputation%2C%20as%20some%20of%20us%20think%20we%20are%20doing%2C%20is%20not%20important%20to%20debate.%20This%20is%20because%20views%20are%20set%20in%20stone%20since%20we%20are%20in%20the%20tenth%20year%20of%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20years%20and%20there%20is%20sufficient%20evidence%20to%20convince%20someone%20one%20way%20or%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20more%20interesting%20is%20to%20examine%20what%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20policy%20actually%20is%20and%20what%20it%20is%20intended%20to%20achieve.%20In%202014%2C%20the%20BJP%20manifesto%20said%20it%20would%20%E2%80%9Cstrengthen%20SAARC%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20states%20%E2%80%9Cwill%20be%20encouraged%20to%20play%20a%20greater%20role%20in%20diplomacy%E2%80%9D.%20For%20instance%2C%20Punjab%2C%20which%20overwhelmingly%20suffers%20when%20Canadian%20visas%20are%20affected%2C%20would%20caution%20New%20Delhi%20on%20foreign%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20both%20these%20references%20were%20eliminated.%20No%20fresh%20text%20replaced%20it%20but%20those%20who%20study%20foreign%20policy%20praised%20a%20new%20approach%20that%20they%20saw%20coming%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20approach%20comes%20from%20a%20series%20of%20speeches%20made%20by%20Subrahmanyam%20Jaishankar%20on%20things%20as%20diverse%20as%20China%E2%80%99s%20rise%20to%20power%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20lost%20decades%2C%20the%20Mahabharata%2C%20maritime%20power%20and%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThese%20assorted%20speeches%20were%20compiled%20into%20a%20book%2C%20called%20%3Cem%3EThe%20India%20Way%3A%20Strategies%20for%20an%20Uncertain%20World%3C%2Fem%3E.%20What%20are%20these%20strategies%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20Jaishankar%20assumes%20that%20the%20US%20and%20Europe%20will%20continue%20to%20look%20inward%20(his%20book%20was%20published%20just%20before%20Donald%20Trump%20lost%20the%202020%20election)%2C%20while%20China%20would%20continue%20to%20rise.%20This%20would%20open%20the%20space%20for%20countries%20like%20India%20to%20be%20opportunistic%20in%20their%20engagements%20with%20the%20world%20and%20they%20did%20not%20need%20consistency.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhat%20India%20wanted%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmulti-polar%20Asia%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20meaning%20one%20in%20which%20India%20could%20claim%20parity%20with%20China.%20Many%20balls%20would%20need%20to%20be%20kept%20in%20the%20air%20(Jaishankar%20has%20a%20fondness%20for%20stock%20phrases)%20and%20India%20would%20handle%20them%20with%20dexterity.%20This%20was%20opportunism%2C%20but%20that%20was%20all%20right%20because%20opportunism%20was%20India%E2%80%99s%20culture.%20The%20Mahabharata%E2%80%99s%20lessons%2C%20Jaishankar%20says%2C%20are%20that%20deceit%20and%20immorality%20are%20merely%20to%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20play%20by%20the%20rules%E2%80%9D.%20Drona%E2%80%99s%20demanding%20of%20Eklavya%E2%80%99s%20thumb%2C%20Indra%E2%80%99s%20appropriation%20of%20Karna%E2%80%99s%20armour%2C%20Arjuna%20using%20Shikhandi%20as%20a%20human%20shield%2C%20these%20were%20but%20%E2%80%9Cpractices%20and%20traditions%E2%80%9D.%20Inconsistency%20in%20policy%20was%20not%20only%20fine%20but%20required%20because%20%E2%80%9Cobsessing%20about%20consistency%E2%80%9D%20made%20little%20sense%20in%20changing%20circumstances.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20was%20such%20a%20doctrine%20to%20be%20called%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20speech%20he%20made%20where%20he%20first%20laid%20out%20this%20doctrine%20of%20opportunism%20and%20inconsistency%2C%20Jaishankar%20said%20it%20is%20hard%20to%20give%20it%20a%20name.%20He%20takes%20up%20and%20discards%20the%20phrases%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9Cmulti-alignment%E2%80%9D%20(%E2%80%9Csounds%20too%20opportunistic%E2%80%9D)%20and%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20first%E2%80%9D%20(%E2%80%9Csounds%20self-centred%E2%80%9D).%20He%20settles%20at%20%E2%80%9Cadvancing%20prosperity%20and%20influence%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20he%20says%20is%20accurate%20but%20admits%20is%20not%20catchy.%20He%20believes%20that%20some%20name%20will%20eventually%20come%20if%20it%20is%20pursued%20long%20enough%2C%20because%20part%20of%20the%20challenge%20is%20that%20we%20are%20still%20in%20the%20early%20phase%20of%20a%20major%20transition.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20that%20is%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnother%20reason%20that%20he%20was%20unable%20to%20come%20up%20with%20a%20name%20for%20it%20as%20clean%20and%20understandable%20as%2C%20say%2C%20%E2%80%9Cnon-alignment%E2%80%9D%2C%20could%20be%20that%20this%20was%20no%20real%20foreign%20policy%20at%20all.%20The%20problems%20that%20have%20been%20listed%20at%20the%20top%20of%20this%20article%20reflect%20this%20lack%20of%20coherence%20and%20effectiveness.%20Buying%20cheap%20Russian%20oil%20when%20nobody%20is%20stopping%20you%20from%20doing%20so%20is%20not%20a%20foreign%20policy%2C%20but%20it%20was%20praised%20as%20being%20that.%20A%20rotating%20presidency%20of%20the%20G-20%20was%20not%20an%20achievement%2C%20but%20that%20is%20how%20it%20was%20sold%20to%20Indians.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhat%20interested%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20and%20what%20made%20for%20pageant%20and%20ceremony%2C%20was%20being%20passed%20off%20as%20something%20meaningful.%20It%20is%20not%20easy%20to%20escape%20the%20conclusion%20that%20Jaishankar%20provided%20the%20sophistry%20to%20cover%20what%20was%20essentially%20random%20and%20directionless%20behaviour%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20passing%20off%20as%20foreign%20policy%20strategy.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJaishankar%20says%20that%20this%20nameless%20policy%20of%20his%20is%20intended%20to%20achieve%20four%20outcomes.%20Greater%20prosperity%20at%20home%3B%20peace%20on%20the%20borders%3B%20protection%20of%20Indians%20and%20enhanced%20influence%20abroad.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOnce%20again%2C%20there%20is%20no%20point%20in%20going%20through%20what%20is%20happening%20on%20the%20borders%20or%20on%20prosperity.%20The%20issue%20is%20whether%20having%20examined%20what%20we%20have%20tried%20to%20achieve%20and%20looking%20at%20what%20results%20around%20us%2C%20we%20should%20reassess%20what%20India%E2%80%99s%20role%20in%20the%20world%20is%20and%20whether%20we%20are%20doing%20the%20right%20thing%20for%20ourselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698770719000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F26083945%2FF6NVFb_XAAAuHrW.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findias-behaviour-on-the-world-stage-is-not-helping-its-interests%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22What%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20policy%20actually%20is%20and%20what%20it%20is%20intended%20to%20achieve%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A22%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findias-behaviour-on-the-world-stage-is-not-helping-its-interests%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%20Says%20It%20Is%20'Leader'%20of%20Global%20South%20But%20UN's%20Gaza%20Vote%20Shows%20It%20Has%20No%20Followers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F31202909%2Fisrael-palestine.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20landslide%20numbers%20with%20which%20the%20UN%20General%20Assembly%20(UNGA)%20passed%20a%20resolution%20to%20call%20for%20a%20%E2%80%98humanitarian%20pause%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20violence%20in%20West%20Asia%20has%20certainly%20been%20an%20effective%20demonstration%20of%20international%20public%20opinion%2C%20especially%20from%20the%20Global%20South.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20October%2027%2C%20121%20nations%20voted%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20resolution%20sponsored%20by%20Jordan%20and%20the%20Arab%20Group%2C%20while%2014%20voted%20against%20it%20and%2044%20abstained%20from%20voting%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Iraq%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenationalnews.com%2Fmena%2Fpalestine-israel%2F2023%2F10%2F28%2Firaq-blames-technical-fault-for-gaza-ceasefire-vote-mix-up-at-un-general-assembly%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Echanged%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20its%20vote%20from%20abstention%20to%20%E2%80%98Yes%E2%80%99%20later%2C%20citing%20technical%20difficulties.%20Most%20of%20the%20Global%20South%20voted%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20resolution%2C%20while%20the%20West%20largely%20voted%20negatively%20or%20abstained.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20vote%20took%20place%20around%20three%20weeks%20after%20Hamas%20launched%20a%20terror%20attack%20inside%20Israel%20which%20killed%20around%201%2C400%20people.%20In%20retaliation%2C%20Israel%20unleashed%20a%20massive%20campaign%20of%20airstrikes%20followed%20by%20ground%20operations%20in%20the%20past%20few%20days.%20Over%20an%20estimated%208%2C000%20people%20have%20been%20killed%20in%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20so%20far.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20UNGA%20vote%20marked%20a%20notable%20change%20in%20comparison%20to%20the%20situation%20after%20February%202022%2C%20when%20the%20Global%20South%20largely%20aligned%20with%20West-backed%20resolutions%20criticising%20Russia%20for%20its%20invasion%20of%20%C2%A0Ukraine.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20the%20growing%20resentment%20over%20the%20rising%20costs%20of%20fuel%20and%20fertiliser%20%E2%80%93%20as%20a%20result%20of%20the%20Ukraine%20war%20%E2%80%93%20did%20lead%20to%20Western%20countries%20publicly%20acknowledging%20the%20price%20being%20paid%20by%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world.%20India%2C%20which%20has%20abstained%20from%20all%20UN%20resolutions%20that%20criticised%20Russia%20for%20the%20Ukraine%20war%2C%20had%20also%20sought%20to%20take%20the%20mantle%20of%20the%20Global%20South%E2%80%99s%20leadership%20by%20highlighting%20the%20disproportionate%20economic%20hardship%20being%20borne%20by%20Asia%2C%20Africa%20and%20Latin%20America.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20October%2027%20vote%20has%20brought%20into%20focus%20even%20more%20forcefully%20the%20stark%20difference%20between%20the%20Global%20South%20and%20the%20Global%20North.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FZfpdL%2F7%2F%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22700%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Voting%20Record%20for%20UNGA%20resolution%20on%20Gaza%20ceasefire%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22419%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fopinion%2Fcolumns%2Fisrael-palestine-conflict-ghaza-israel-war-muslim-countries-stand-on-palestine-9006499%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWriting%20in%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EIndian%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EExpress%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Pratap%20Bhanu%20Mehta%20observed%20that%20despite%20the%20heightened%20concerns%20about%20a%20wider%20conflict%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthere%20is%20not%20one%20significant%20world%20leader%20who%20is%20acting%20in%20a%20way%20that%20is%20not%20morally%20myopic%20or%20politically%20ill-judged%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20his%20scathing%20critique%20of%20leaders%20ranging%20from%20the%20US%20president%20and%20European%20leaders%20to%20Arab%20regimes%20and%20China%2C%20he%20also%20highlighted%20how%20India%E2%80%99s%20self-professed%20leadership%20of%20the%20Global%20South%20has%20not%20gathered%20any%20support%20on%20such%20a%20key%20issue%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20for%20India%2C%20one%20anecdote%20will%20suffice.%20I%20was%20at%20an%20international%20meeting%20recently%2C%20where%20someone%2C%20not%20unsympathetic%20to%20India%2C%20asked%20this%20question%3A%20%E2%80%98India%20claims%20to%20be%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20Global%20South.%20But%20let%20us%20ask%20the%20question%2C%20%E2%80%98who%20is%20following%20it%3F%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20better%20understand%20this%20gulf%20between%20India%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20Global%20South%2C%20The%20Wire%20spoke%20to%20Sarang%20Shidore%2C%3Cspan%3E%20director%20of%20the%20Global%20South%20Program%20at%20the%20Washington-based%20Quincy%20Institute.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShidore%20noted%20that%20there%20was%20a%20greater%20consensus%20among%20the%20developing%20world%20about%20the%20response%20to%20the%20situation%20in%20Gaza%2C%20with%20the%20notable%20exceptions%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Findia-refuses-to-back-landslide-un-general-assembly-call-for-humanitarian-truce-in-gaza%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20Philippines.%20The%20other%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fglobalsarang%2Fstatus%2F1718339406753362159%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eanomaly%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20was%20the%20cluster%20of%20Pacific%20Island%20states%2C%20although%20they%20tend%20to%20vote%20with%20the%20US%20on%20many%20international%20issues.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20Philippines%2C%20aligned%20with%20the%20West%2C%20abstained%20because%20it%20said%20it%20recognised%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cright%20to%20self-defence%E2%80%9D%2C%20what%20raised%20eyebrows%20across%20the%20Global%20South%20was%20India%E2%80%99s%20refusal%20to%20back%20the%20UNGA%20call%20for%20a%20humanitarian%20pause.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20claimed%20that%20it%20didn%E2%80%99t%20vote%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20UNGA%20resolution%20because%20the%20text%20didn%E2%80%99t%20explicitly%20criticise%20the%20October%207%20terror%20attack%20by%20Hamas.%20Incidentally%2C%20India%20has%20not%20mentioned%20Hamas%20in%20any%20of%20its%20public%20statements%2C%20including%20its%20Explanation%20of%20Vote.%20As%20an%20aside%2C%20the%20last%20time%20that%20Hamas%20was%20mentioned%20by%20India%20was%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fmedia-briefings.htm%3Fdtl%2F3466%2Fstatement%2Bby%2Bofficial%2Bspokesman%2Bon%2Bthe%2Bkilling%2Bof%2Bhamas%2Bleader%2Babdel%2Baziz%2Brantisi%5C%22%20data-stringify-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fmedia-briefings.htm%3Fdtl%2F3466%2Fstatement%2Bby%2Bofficial%2Bspokesman%2Bon%2Bthe%2Bkilling%2Bof%2Bhamas%2Bleader%2Babdel%2Baziz%2Brantisi%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20data-sk%3D%5C%22tooltip_parent%5C%22%3EApril%202004%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20when%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20said%20that%20the%20targeted%20assassination%20of%20Hamas%20leader%20Abdel%20Aziz%20Rantisi%20was%20%E2%80%9Cunjustified%20and%20unacceptable%20and%20cannot%20be%20condoned%20under%20any%20circumstances%E2%80%9D.%20%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%2C%20as%20now%2C%20the%20party%20in%20power%20in%20India%20was%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party.%20%3Cspan%3ERantisi%20was%20killed%20by%20the%20Israeli%20Air%20Force.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELast%20week%20at%20the%20UN%2C%20India%20was%20the%20only%20South%20Asian%20country%20to%20not%20vote%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20resolution.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20Philippines%20was%20the%20only%20Southeast%20Asian%20country%20to%20not%20vote%20positively%2C%20with%20Cambodia%20not%20recording%20its%20vote.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20Shidore%2C%20the%20global%20south%20strongly%20wants%20the%20war%20to%20end%20and%20has%20been%20critical%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20actions.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fglobalsarang%2Fstatus%2F1718339408053596169%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20estimates%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20in%20the%20Global%20South%2C%20outside%20West%20Asia%2C%20more%20than%2070%25%20of%20countries%20voted%20in%20favour%20of%20Jordan%E2%80%99s%20resolution%2C%20while%20around%2023%25%20abstained%20and%20only%20around%207%25%20voted%20against.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBreaking%20it%20down%20geographically%2C%20he%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fglobalsarang%2Fstatus%2F1718339405323137431%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enoted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%2030%20African%20countries%2C%2026%20Latin%20American%20countries%2C%20nine%20Southeast%20Asian%20countries%20and%20five%20South%20Asian%20countries%20had%20voted%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20resolution.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20following%20is%20an%20edited%20version%20of%20the%20interview%20conducted%20via%20e-mail.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20it%20correct%20to%20say%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20this%20UNGA%20resolution%2C%20that%20there%20is%20even%20greater%20divergence%20from%20the%20West%20and%20a%20more%20unified%20consensus%20in%20the%20Global%20South%20in%20the%20latest%20eruption%20of%20the%20Israel-Palestine%20dispute%20compared%20to%20the%20Ukraine%20war%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYes%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20(West%20Asia)%20among%20its%C2%A0citizenry.%20Middle%20Eastern%20governments%20however%20remain%20more%20ambivalent%2C%20but%20they%20are%20being%20forced%20into%20a%20more%20critical%20stance%20toward%20Israel%20and%20the%20US%20due%20to%20public%20pressure.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20your%20analysis%20of%20the%20voting%20record%20of%20the%20Global%20South%20to%20the%20October%2027%20UNGA%20resolution%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20analysis%20is%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fglobalsarang%2Fstatus%2F1718339398205424004%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emy%20Twitter%20thread%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20noteworthy%20additional%20element%20is%20that%20several%20Global%20South%20states%20%E2%80%93%20largely%20in%20Latin%20America%2C%20though%20also%20key%20African%20ones%20such%20as%20Kenya%20and%20Nigeria%20%E2%80%93%20preferred%20to%20add%20language%20proposed%20by%20the%20US%20and%20Canada%20condemning%20Hamas%20and%20mentioning%20Israeli%20hostages%2C%20but%20this%20preference%20was%20not%20a%20barrier%20in%20their%20clear%20support%20for%20the%20adopted%20resolution%20calling%20for%20a%20%E2%80%9Chumanitarian%20truce%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20factors%20have%20driven%20such%20a%20robust%20response%20from%20Global%20South%20members%3F%20Is%20it%20rooted%20in%20a%20perception%20of%20Western%20hypocrisy%2C%20considerations%20of%20domestic%20public%20opinion%2C%20or%20national%20interests%20and%20external%20influences%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPublic%20opinion%20is%20a%20strong%20factor%C2%A0in%20the%20Middle%20East.%20The%20view%20that%20the%20US%20practices%20double%20standards%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20conflict%20and%20human%20rights%20is%20by%20now%20well-known%20across%20the%20non-Western%20world%20and%20understood%2C%20but%20the%20Gaza%20crisis%20will%20only%20further%20entrench%20this%20perception.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20it%20reasonable%20to%20anticipate%20that%20the%20growing%20prominence%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98Global%20South%E2%80%99%20in%20discussions%20will%20bring%20about%20a%20shift%20in%20policies%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20this%20war%20lasts%20much%20longer%20or%20escalates%2C%20the%20Middle%20Eastern%20governments%20may%20take%20further%20steps%20and%20there%20could%20be%20a%20major%20realignment%20away%20from%20the%20US%20%E2%80%93%20but%20we%20are%20not%20there%20yet.%20In%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20Global%20South%2C%20this%20is%20one%20of%20many%20factors%20that%20is%20increasing%20alienation%20from%20the%20West%2C%20though%20it%20is%20still%20incremental.%20The%20other%20important%20point%20here%20is%20that%20not%20all%20Global%20South%20states%20are%20following%20this%20trend.%20India%20and%20the%20Philippines%20are%20two%20major%20exceptions%20%E2%80%93%20both%20have%20been%20relatively%20sympathetic%20to%20Israeli%20and%20US%20positions%20on%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20400px)%2085vw%2C%20400px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F31202656%2FL1UHcYgb_400x400.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2