.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2Fsustainable-home-1-1698759499-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2Fsustainable-home-1-1698759499-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2Fsustainable-home-1-1698759499-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-333366%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EIn%20their%20new%20home%2C%20Ramachandrudu%20and%20Bharani%20embrace%20an%20eco-friendly%20lifestyle.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20container%20house%20boasts%20two%20bedrooms%2C%20a%20drawing%20room%2C%20two%20bathrooms%2C%20and%20a%20staircase.%20Also%2C%20they%20opted%20to%20use%20styrofoam%20as%20an%20effective%20insulating%20material%20for%20the%20containers.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20Bharani%20has%20also%20made%20a%20shed%20from%20styrofoam.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20first%20crushed%20styrofoam%20and%20mixed%20it%20with%20cement%20to%20make%20bricks.%20If%20the%20red%20brick%20weighs%203.3%20kg%2C%20the%20styrofoam%20one%20would%20weigh%20nearly%202.5%20kg.%20The%20advantage%20of%20using%20such%20bricks%20is%20that%20close%20to%2070%20percent%20of%20the%20brick%20is%20made%20from%20scrap%3B%20this%20saves%20top%20soil%20which%20is%20usually%20exploited%20during%20construction%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%2029-year-old%20tells%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETalking%20about%20his%20decision%20to%20join%20his%20father%E2%80%99s%20initiative%2C%20Bharani%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CYoungsters%20are%20still%20not%20completely%20aware%20of%20the%20nitty-gritty%20of%20sustainable%20living%20and%20mostly%20find%20themselves%20engrossed%20in%20a%20fast-paced%20lifestyle.%20Nonetheless%2C%20everyone%20should%20be%20encouraged%20to%20live%20a%20green%20life.%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20free%20from%20the%20rat%20race%20and%20lead%